Intentionally NOT vendored
--------------------------

  - server.ts       — Bun HTTP daemon entry point (T3 exposes its own
                      /api/browser REST endpoint instead)
  - cli.ts          — browse CLI (T3 drives the library directly, no CLI)
  - find-browse.ts  — daemon discovery (no daemon to discover)
  - welcome.html    — daemon's welcome page asset
  - extension/      — Chrome side-panel extension (deferred to a future
                      T3 iteration if the side-panel UX is desired)

No code inside the retained 26 files references any of the above, so the
module graph is complete.

Deviations from upstream behaviour (T3-owned, live outside core/)
----------------------------------------------------------------

Changes T3 needs (per-project Chromium profiles, custom data directories,
agent-facing REST shape, etc.) are implemented in T3-authored files that
live alongside core/ — typically wrappers, subclasses of `BrowserManager`,
or layer code in `apps/server/src/browser/Layers/`. The vendored files
themselves are never edited.
